UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1587
1 WHEREAS, the troops took fire when they arrived, and one of the helicopters was
2 hit but still able to fly. The apprehension force descended into Maduro's compound and
3 moved with speed, precision, and discipline, according to Airforce General Dan Caine,
4 the Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff; and
5 WHEREAS, as the elite Delta Force flooded in, President Maduro attempted to flee
6 to a safe room but never made it inside the door. Delta Force was there too quickly for
7 the door to close and President Maduro and his wife, Cilia Flores, were apprehended with
8 no United States military force fatalities; and
9 WHEREAS, the decisive action and planning of the executive orders to capture
10 President Maduro and his wife were aided in no small part by the Commonwealth of
11 Kentucky providing the replica of the military safe house compound for practice of the
12 mission and the Fort Campbell "Night Stalkers" of the 160th Special Operations Aviation
13 Regiment; and
14 WHEREAS, the members of the elite Delta Force are commended for their
15 effectiveness and efficiency in carrying out sensitive missions throughout the world;
16 NOW, THEREFORE,
17 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
18 Kentucky:
19 Section 1. The Senate hereby recognize the tremendous skill and efficiency of
20 the United States of America's elite Delta Force for the successful capture of Venezuelan
21 President Nicolas Maduro on January 3, 2026.
22 Section 2. When the Senate adjourns this day, it does so in honor of the brave
23 servicemembers who fight for our freedoms.
24 Section 3. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
25 Resolution to Senator Phillip Wheeler.
